The Statue of Liberty was evacuated Friday afternoon in the wake of a bomb threat resulting in a suspicious package being found .
Some 2,700 tourists were rushed off Liverty Island after a 911 caller said he was ` going to blow up ' the landmark .
Police sniffer dogs then seized on a locker on the island , they thought contained something suspicious .
Tour operators said that all 2,,700 evacuees were offered refunds and the park would be open as normal Saturday .